From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: MedyMa build <build@bpi-r4>
Date: Mon, 01 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] mediatek: filogic: bpi-r4: add WiFi LED netdev trigger

Wire the BPI-R4 blue front-panel LED (GPIO 63, sysfs "blue:indicator")
to the 2.4 GHz wireless interface phy0-ap0 so it blinks on WiFi TX/RX
activity instead of running a kernel heartbeat.

The "blue:indicator" sysfs path depends on patch
998-bpi-r4-be14000-leds-fix.patch which changes the DTS LED function
from LED_FUNCTION_WPS to LED_FUNCTION_INDICATOR.
---
 target/linux/mediatek/filogic/base-files/etc/board.d/01_leds | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/target/linux/mediatek/filogic/base-files/etc/board.d/01_leds b/target/linux/mediatek/filogic/base-files/etc/board.d/01_leds
--- a/target/linux/mediatek/filogic/base-files/etc/board.d/01_leds
+++ b/target/linux/mediatek/filogic/base-files/etc/board.d/01_leds
@@ -100,7 +100,8 @@
 bananapi,bpi-r4|\
 bananapi,bpi-r4-poe)
 	ucidef_set_led_netdev "wan" "wan" "mt7530-0:00:green:lan" "wan" "link tx rx"
 	ucidef_set_led_netdev "lan1" "lan1" "mt7530-0:01:green:lan" "lan1" "link tx rx"
 	ucidef_set_led_netdev "lan2" "lan2" "mt7530-0:02:green:lan" "lan2" "link tx rx"
 	ucidef_set_led_netdev "lan3" "lan3" "mt7530-0:03:green:lan" "lan3" "link tx rx"
+	ucidef_set_led_netdev "wlan" "WiFi" "blue:indicator" "phy0-ap0"
 	;;
